cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.SY 

The paper deals with a stochastic multiplayer multi-armed bandit problem, which involves communication and information sharing among players. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to information theory (cs.IT), game theory (cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SY). Among these, cs.IT and cs.GT seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper involves communication protocols and decision-making strategies in a multi-player setting.
